Preheat your oven to 220°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Pop the aubergine and @premium tomato mix{125%g} on a large #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{} and @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, toss to coat then spread out and roast until soft and charred, ~{15-18%minutes}. In a small #bowl{}, soak the @sundried tomatoes{30%g} in hot water.

Meanwhile, tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and pop on another baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Drain the sundried tomatoes and roughly chop.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add the shallot. Fry until soft, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and sundried tomatoes. Fry for another ~{1%minute} then add the lentils to the pan and stir together. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and turn the heat to low.

Meanwhile, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and @honey{15%ml} in a large #mixing bowl{} along with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Tip the lentil mixture into the bowl with the dressing along with the roasted aubergine and tomatoes. Toss to coat and allow to sit for a minute to absorb all the flavours. Just before serving, toss through the @wild rocket{40%g} and @croutons{}.

Divide the salad between your bowls and crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} over the top. Enjoy!